        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Hello!<BR>I'm Greywind from BCK level 44 scout. <BR>The issue I want to address is <b>UNIT</b>.<BR>Game gives us <BR>- Group. Actual basic fighting/hunting unit with means to help, monitor, communicate and of course share loot/points. IMHO 80% of the time group made up of total strangers. Players who do not have training to work together as group.  19% it’s guild group may or may not train together and have wide range of levels and classes. Made only on availability. </P><P>- Guild. Main Unit. Establish hierarchy, easy communication, will provide with shared vault and housing. Main resources of guild are not in game system. It's a guild website and history of playing other games. Basically most of guilds are social clubs with main asset – Long history and trust.</P><P>- Alliance. Provide with communication. Basically point of cooperation between guilds. I don’t know if it provides structure. Our alliance has a web side to provide better corporation. We do cooperate and have events and make alliance group for hunt and fight using /as communication and web.</P><P>- Realm. Last and ultimate organization. We all share same fate. Game system provides more and more reasons for us to work together for common goal.</P><P>I believe the key to success in RvR is in creating fighting unit <b>MILITARY TYPE</b>.<BR>Unit made up from same level and classes which complement each other. <BR>It could be<BR>Heavy cavalry unit Bard, Cleric, Paladin and 5 heavy fighters<BR>Nukers unit made up from casters <BR>Patrol Bard, Infiltrator, Fighter<BR>Commando unit scouts, infiltrators, bard<BR>When we have this it possible to step up to next level make group tactically work with each other and manage troops position.</P><P>It’s not possible even for big guild given different time slot we play but may be broad alliance can do this.</P><P>Alliance broad base could be use to re-organize how we level up and cooperate on mid level battlefields and recruit new members.<BR>For example if we make or re-organize existing guild to be only for level 30-35 it would (IMHO) provide with better communication with each other and consequently with better training, leveling, RvR results, RP.<BR>I have to finish right here. Till next time</P><P><BR></font></td>

