        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Well I don't know if folks would be happy leaving Akalabeth even for a short time. You hafta remember, it takes usually 60 days to become a full member of Akalabeth so there is a strong idea of pride and sense of community that comes with our guild.</P><P>These are great ideas Greywind and I've always thought military style units would do well in RVR situations. We used specific unit tactics when we played WW2Online (bwahaha) and we did quite well against the enemy. To sum this point up, Cremson told me the other day (and this is quite true) one of the key elements to RVR groups is knowing who the Chief is and who the Indians are (this is an old American saying).</P><P>I think if anything, having a "boot camp" of the newer RVR folks to get them some RVR exposure would be nice. But how many these days dont have RVR exposure? Since they added the Battlegrounds, even our level 20ish characters are getting decent combat experience.</P><P><img src="http://www.kgmedia.com/uploads/nazzire_sig.gif" border=0><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
