        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Greywind,</P><P>I'm not sure that forming level-based guilds would be practical, though you make a good case for it.</P><P>I am interested, though, in what types of groups people have found from EXPERIENCE work well in RvR.  I've seen many people put forward ideas similar to the ones you mention (casters here, heavy tanks there, etc).  OTOH, what I've heard from the uberguild folks with tons of RvR experience is that a good, balanced RvR group looks a lot like a good, balanced PvE group.  2-3 tanks, 2 healers minimum, ideally Bladeturn and Crowd Control as well.  For RvR, toss in Speedsong and a few Stealthers.  There you have it; a fully-functional, standalone fighting unit.</P><P>How about something like these:</P><P>G1 - First Blood<BR>(Scouts ahead of G2 - takes out snipers if possible - self-resses if possible, but does not wait for LD's - carries 1 ram if possible.)<BR>Rogue<BR>Archer<BR>Rogue/Archer<BR>Archer/Nuker<BR>Speedsinger<BR>Res'er<BR>Open (2nd Res class?)<BR>Open (Bladeturner?)</P><P>G2 - Heavy Metal<BR>(Follows G1 by ~1 minute - picks up LD's/resses from G1 if needed - carries other siege equipment)<BR>Speedsinger<BR>Bladeturner<BR>Melee1<BR>Melee2<BR>Melee3<BR>Healer1<BR>Healer2<BR>Open</P><P>Cazz, Assassin of Akalabeth<BR>Troll.  The other other white meat.<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
